r UI and front-end expertise to various aspects of the developer \u2018onboarding\u2019 experience. We\u2019re looking for a motivated and versatile self-starter who values a user-centered design approach, has a knack for writing solid front-end code, designing beautiful and functional UIs and an eye for detail \u2013 but with the wisdom to sweat the important details first! What You Will Be Doing Gather and evaluate product requirements in collaboration with project leads, developers, and key stakeholders. Design intuitive and engaging interfaces from the ground up. Implement front-end code for your UIs using modern web technologies like HTML, CSS, and JS. Illustrate visual ideas using sketches, wireframes, mockups and prototypes. Prepare and present working prototypes regularly to internal teams and key stakeholders for feedback and user testing. Support design decisions with best practices and data from usability studies and site metrics. Adhere to and contribute to brand guidelines on typography, iconography, colors, imagery, and graphic style. We're looking for someone who has: A strong portfolio demonstrating 3+ years of experience with a breadth of UI design and development capabilities. Working knowledge of any modern front-end frameworks (we currently use Vue). High level of proficiency in designing UI components with a modular architecture. Extensive knowledge of UI design best practices and current web production techniques and limitations. Experience working in a collaborative team environment, with the ability to work independently and self-directed as necessary. Clear and concise written and oral English communication skills. Nice To Have Proficiency with modern design tools like Figma (our tool of choice) and ability to learn and adapt to new ones. Strong understanding of UX best practices and how to translate them into usable interfaces. Good understanding of component-based design systems and style guides. Ability to design and implement meaningful animated micro-interactions. Interest in emerging interactive technology in web, mobile, and other devices. What We Offer The opportunity to be part of building the future of the Internet Flexible work schedule Excellent benefits like educational budget, fitness and wellbeing spend At least 4 weeks of paid vacation Competitive salary package, including equity Applying To apply, please go through our online application process and include a cover letter with a link to your portfolio. Tendermint In The News https://techcrunch.com/2019/03/17/welcome-to-the-hub-of-all-hubs/ https://cointelegraph.com/news/cross-platform-blockchain-project-cosmos-launches-first-hub-after-17-million-ico https://www.coindesk.com/a-blockchain-to-connect-all-blockchains-cosmos-is-now-officially-live https://www.coindesk.com/how-to-turn-a-17-million-ico-into-104-million-the-cosmos-story ",
